reviews.title: Gunjali Patel
reviews.description: The place is very unhygienic, would not recommend. we went for pre-wedding photo shoot today, the room they provided us wasn’t clean it had dirty foot prints in the room, closet wasn’t cleaned for ages. flush was broken, water was constantly running, we asked for another room but It was same condition. All the sets are poorly maintained, either lights won’t work or the part is broken. On top of it, the staff at the reception isn’t helpful and was very rude. Someone would come to you offer water in old softdrink bottle. If you ask for bottled water then you have to go all the way to restaurant and purchase it, No other option. Zero customer service. Not to mention all the street dogs live there on sets and couch. Not worth to visit due to very unhygienic conditions and poor customer service.Rooms: Very dirty and unhygienic, not maintained,Food & drinks: Taste less food.

reviews.title: Kalpana Tiwari
reviews.description: Yesterday (13th January) I visited place with my family.  We often visited various resorts in past. This was my worst experience of all.Not recommended for one day picnic.Very poor hygiene is maintained here.Poha, upma, bread butter,  banana & tea-coffee was served ( very tasteless!!!)After breakfast, we went to swimming pool. For changing the clothes we went to the wash room. No lights,  broken taps, Very uncomfortable environment.  The smell was very dirty, can't even spend time to change. Gents had changed the clothes outside the wash room ( the smell was unbearable 😫)Swimming pool was good. We enjoyed there for 1.30 hour. Then staff members started calling us for lunch. We changed the clothes in same unhealthy wash area.Meanwhile my daughter went restaurant for water ( she hadn't her phone & purse) The manager asked for 20 rupees. She was returning from restaurant,  I met her on her way.I went there with my daughter & sister.  The manager literally quarreled with us. He was continuously arguing about the lunch time.  Then we left the place without having our lunch.We had already paid the amount i.e. 11,700/- before entering the premises.Very very bad experience !!😞Do think twice before visiting.

reviews.title: Chirag Chauhan
reviews.description: Not Recommended for a one day picnic. Can be a good choice for a photography event  but its not a first choice atleast for me.CONS and PRO are mentioned for each category belowFood : (CONS ONLY)very average or below average Menu at the price point 1300 for Breakfast and Lunch (i did not tried high tea, because i did not like other 2 meals)Breakfast: Tea/ coffee/ milkPoha, Upma(oil and peanutes tasted very bad), Banana, Bread butter sandwich, Cornflakes (this was looking like fried corn flakes chewda 😂)Lunch:Roti, Moong subji, Paneer Subji( correction gravy only, Paneer used for garnishing purpose only), dal fry(Generally Sal fry consistency is thick, this was watery consistency), Rice, Onion Salad, Buttermilk (watery consistency with too much salt to increase the quantity), Khaman and Gulab jamunLunch menu should have been good.Very much disappointed with Quality and the Menu.Restaurant Premise:  it was quite OK place, but the Air conditioning was very poor in the whole area, we were suffocated as it was full house. AC were acting like coolers onlyIndoor - Outdoor games : (CONS)All games are for on paper use only.Indoor games are located in one small hall without AC. and all the indoor games are either broken or damaged or not workingindoor games : air hockey (2, works oy 1)snooker: broken table broken sticks, balls run from corners to centercarrom - did not tryTable Tennis - did not try, but the table net was broken and was in worst place to playOutdoor games:(PRO and CONS)Cricket - can be played but the lawn was not properly fenced like box cricket. was Ok but should have been more betterbadminton- I saw the net placed out side the indoor game area but it was in a passage like garden place and surrounded by small tree plants which makes u to feel awekward while playingYou can not spend more than 1 hour total, even if you want to do for all indoor and outdoor games. This is a must required amenities for one day outingSwimming pool:PRO:quite large area of swimming pool. Loud speakers with song you can enjoy the moments with friends.CONS:People are allowed to enter without swimming costumesCostumes are not available for rent for MALEs. incase available then they are worn out and price is too high(100rs for male, unsure about female constume rates) compared to the consumes qualityNo proper shower facilities or cleanliness or hyigine is not mentained there properlyNo locker facility is provided again disappointed  here.Other Property Atrractions(PRO):Good place for photography like pre wedding or  something else for couples (but not the best place for the same).Huge Resort premises.Final Verdict:If you looking for a resort to enjoy with friends and you want good food and activities and cream croud, you are looking at rhe wrong place.My suggestion would be increase your budget a bit more and under 2000 rs PP there are plenty of resort options available.
